            </li>
            <li><strong>Bird Watching</strong>: With a wide variety of resident and migratory birds, bird watchers are in for a treat.
              <br>
              <img style="max-width: 100%;max-height: 400px;" src="https://redearth.in/blog/wp-content/uploads/2021/07/Birds-in-Tadoba.jpg" >

            </li>
            <li><strong>Tribal Culture</strong>: Visitors can interact with the local tribal communities and learn about their connection
              with the forest.</li>
          </ol>
          <h5>Best Time to Visit</h5>
          <p>The ideal time to visit Tadoba is during the summer months (March to June) when animals frequently visit
            water bodies, increasing the likelihood of sightings. However, the monsoon and winter seasons (October to
            February) offer lush greenery and cooler weather, making it a delightful experience for nature lovers.</p>
          <h5>Responsible Tourism</h5>
          <p>While visiting the Tadoba-Andhari Tiger Reserve, it is crucial to follow the park’s guidelines to ensure
            the conservation of wildlife and their habitat. Avoid littering, respect the animals’ space, and support
            eco-friendly initiatives.</p>
